{{Otheruses|Sector Command}}
{{Quote|The ''Wheel's'' sanctuary is a courtesy of the Empire. As the Empire's chief representative in this sector, I elect to withdraw that courtesy-- until our troopers find and '''slay''' every being on that freighter!|Sector Commander Zertik Strom|<ref name="Star Wars (1977) 18">[[Star Wars (1977) 18|''Star Wars'' (1977) 18]]</ref>}}
'''Sector Commander''' was a title held by [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] personnel responsible for the military forces in a [[Sector/Legends|sector]]. Eventually, as the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] grew in power, its leadership appointed sector commanders in liberated areas.<ref name="DESB">''[[Dark Empire Sourcebook]]''</ref>

==History==
An average sector commander in the Empire had one or more [[Super Star Destroyer/Legends|Super Star Destroyers]] as part of his or her military assets.<ref name="DESB" /> A sector commander was one of the top-ranking officers allowed a full Imperial [[Order of Battle/Legends|Order of Battle]].<ref name="BTS">''[[Before the Storm]]''</ref>
[[Zertik Strom/Legends|Zertik Strom]] was a sector commander of the military forces in the [[Sector/Legends|sector]] containing the [[Besh Gorgon system/Legends|Besh Gorgon system]] and [[The Wheel/Legends|the ''Wheel'']].<ref name="SW20:D">[[Star Wars (1977) 20|''Star Wars'' (1977) 20]]</ref> At some point, the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] began to appoint sector commanders in regions of space that they controlled. One such commander was [[Callus]], who oversaw the [[Mortex sector/Legends|Mortex sector]].

